KENYAN Ministry of Health has confirmed 45 new Covid-19 cases on Tuesday as infections in the East African Member State rose to 535. Capital FM quoted Health Cabinet Secretary Mutahi Kabwe as saying: “We have the highest number today and that shows how serious this pandemic is in our country…….We have 45 confirmed cases from tests conducted in the last 24 hours.” Despite of the increase, CS Mutahi released good news to Kenyans after reported that nine people had been discharged from hospital, raising number of recoveries to 182. He explained that, out of 45 new cases, 29 were from Nairobi.